title: New Zealand Changes in Inventories
description: The stocks of goods held by firms in New Zealand increased by 29 NZD Million in the second quarter of 2022. Changes in Inventories in New Zealand averaged 182.09 NZD Million from 1987 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 1822 NZD Million in the third quarter of 2021 and a record low of -1012 NZD Million in the second quarter of 2009. In New Zealand, changes in inventories are often a leading indicator for the overall performance of the economy. This page provides the latest reported value for - New Zealand Changes in Inventories - plus previous releases, historical high and low, short-term forecast and long-term prediction, economic calendar, survey consensus and news.
author: Statistics New Zealand
